# Lesson candidate: harvester false-CRITICAL flood from live-source transients

**Date:** 2026-06-20
**Source:** Gamma_Conductor fire (Saturday after-hours)
**Theme fit:** C7 (silent success/noise — audit outputs, not exit codes) + OP-22 (compound, don't accumulate)

## Symptom
`automation/overnight/queue.md` accumulated 24 phantom `## CRITICAL` HARVEST-REGFAIL
rows overnight (2026-06-19T22:27 .. 2026-06-20T09:57, one per half-hourly run), each
showing the SAME 14 `.live`/parity stages failing at `passed=74/88`. Every future
conductor fire would read 24 CRITICALs at the top of the queue and be misled into
thinking the engine was on fire. Nothing ever drains them.

## Root cause
`crypto/benchmarks/gym_harvester.py::_detect_regression_fail` emitted a CRITICAL the
moment `overall_pass is False`, with no discrimination between a deterministic code
regression and an environmental transient. When the live data feed is briefly
unreachable (network blip / rate-limit), EVERY `.live` validator fails at once →
`overall_pass=false` → CRITICAL emitted. It self-heals on the next run (verified:
live gym was 90/90 overall_pass=true an hour after the last phantom row), but the
queue rows are append-only and persist.

## Fix (shipped this fire)
Producer guard: a stage failure is only a reproducible regression if the stage is
DETERMINISTIC (`.offline`/`.fixture`). `_detect_regression_fail` now suppresses the
CRITICAL when ALL failed stages are `.live`/known-flaky (`v02_source_parity`,
`v15_three_source_parity.live`); it fires only when ≥1 deterministic stage fails, or
when no `per_stage` breakdown exists to classify (conservative). Mirrors the existing
v02/v15 KNOWN_FLAKY_LIVE_SOURCE carve-out already used by `runner.py` overall_pass and
`_detect_source_disagreement`. Guarded by
`test_gym_harvester.py::test_regression_fail_suppressed_when_only_live_stages_fail`
(+ `_emits_when_per_stage_missing`). The 24 stale rows were pruned and archived
verbatim to `automation/overnight/queue-archive-2026-06-20.md`.

## Generalizable principle
An auto-queue producer that fires CRITICAL on a non-deterministic (live/source-dependent)
signal will flood the backlog with un-drainable noise on every transient. CRITICAL must
be reserved for reproducible, deterministic failures. Classify environmental vs
deterministic at the producer, not by hoping a downstream triage prunes it.
